## ðŸš€ How to Start the FastAPI Backend Manually

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/your-repo.git
cd your-repo
```

### 2. (Recommended) Create and activate a virtual environment

**On Mac/Linux:**
```bash
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
```

**On Windows:**
```bash
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate
```

### 3. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install fastapi uvicorn
```

### 4. Start the FastAPI backend server
```bash
uvicorn disaster_relief_chatbot:app --reload
```
- The server will run at [http://127.0.0.1:8000](http://127.0.0.1:8000)
- **Keep this terminal window open** while you use the chatbot.

### 5. Test the backend
Open your browser and go to [http://127.0.0.1:8000/ping].  
You should see a JSON response confirming the server is online.

---

**Note:**  
You must manually start the backend server each time you want to use the chatbot locally.  
If you close the terminal or stop the server, the backend will no longer be available until you start it again.
